<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>17 February 2006</title></head><body><div><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">St George’s, University of London (SGUL) (WSC078)</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Summary</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">- </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SGUL</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is an institute of higher education and research directly impacted by Sally Davies announcement linking funding to Athena Swan status</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">- The process of applying for Athena Swan funding has been a </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">positive experience, and we recommend government commit to maintaining the link between funding and accreditation.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Introduction</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1. We are pleased to respond to the Science and Technology Committee (Commons) inquiry into Women in STEM Careers.  We hope </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">this information is useful to you as you work on your review.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">About SGUL</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">2. SGUL is a college of the University of London training medical, biomedical science, nursing, radiography, and physiotherapy students.  Our award-winning undergraduate and graduate</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> recruitment schemes ensure the next generation of health-care workers reflects our community.  SGUL is also a post-graduate research institute, specializing in translational research </span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Impact of Sally Davies announcement on SGUL</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">3. We would like to thank </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Sally Davies for her concrete commitment to gender equality in science.  In particular, we fully support her announcement regarding the future link between measurable improvements in institutional equality and NIHR research funding.  The requirement for an</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> Athena Silver award impacts directly on our institution, as NIHR is a significant source of our income.  We are able to make a stronger case for important</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> improvements as a direct result, as summarized below.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">4. Our initial application for an Athena Bro</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">nze award was submitted in November 2012.  We received useful feedback from the Athena Swan committee, and it has been very valuable to compare ourselves to other institutions.  </span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">5. Our next submission for an Athena Bronze award will be in November 2013, </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and this has been given high priority at the management level, and is discussed on all key committees.  Quality data has been collected regarding staff job descriptions, promotions, recruitment and flexible working.  This data was previously not available </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">and has flagged up areas of concern.  Transparency regarding senior committee appointments and decision making is improving.  A wide variety of actions has been implemented or will be proposed in our bid in order to support the working environment for wome</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">n at SGUL.  These include job descriptions, promotion and recruitment processes, role models, mentoring, networking opportunities, flexible work plans and maternity leave.  In addition to the required Self-Assessment Team, we also have a large group of ent</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">husiastic volunteers for our Athena Swan Action Group.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">6. SGUL acknowledges that we are still in the early stages of our aim for an Athena Silver Award, but progress so far is encouraging.  The direct link between future funding and the Award has focussed</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> minds and ensured support from a broader range of SGUL staff and management.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">7. We anticipate that Athena Swan will in the future extend to include ethnic diversity.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Role of Government</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">8. Linking research funding to an accredited programme for departme</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ntal or research institutions regarding the role of women (such as Athena Swan) should be mandatory.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">9. Research councils set the funding and the research agenda.  They should have policy statements on funding equality, and release information on grant aw</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ardees at least annually.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>